Case 1-Eur-Bulgaria-Stara Zagora-Bust-Ceramic-6th Millennium BCE-Neolithic

Fig. 1. Bulgaria-Stara Zagora-Bust-Ceramic-6th Millennium BCE-Neolithic

Case no.: 1

Accession Number: A000

Formal Label: Bulgaria-Stara Zagora-Bust-Ceramic-6th Millennium BCE-Neolithic

Display Description:

A hollow ceramic with suspension holes on either side suggesting its use was as a pendant.

LC Classification:

Date or Time Horizon: 6th Millennium BCE-Neolithic

Geographical Area:

Map:

Fig. 2. Map of location of Stara Zagora, Bulgaria. From http://latitude.to/lat/42.42604/lng/25.63356

GPS coordinates: 4225'33.74" N 2538'0.81" E

Cultural Affiliation: 6th Millennium BCE-Neolithic

Medium: ceramic

Dimensions: H 50 mm, W 33 mm

Weight: 34 g

Condition: ceramic replica

Provenance: original, Stara Zagora

Discussion:

The original was found in the ruins of a Neolithic settlement in the region of Stara Zagora, Bulgaria the Original is on display in the Archaeological Museum in Stara Zagora.

References:
